## Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the tvde-manager project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**
- `package.json` - Added `@vercel/speed-insights` v2.0.0 as a dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and its dependencies (459 packages)
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Integrated SpeedInsights component into the root layout

**Implementation Details:**

1. **Package Installation**: Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` v2.0.0 using npm, which is the project's package manager.

2. **Component Integration**: Added the `SpeedInsights` component to the root layout file (`src/app/layout.tsx`) following Next.js App Router best practices:
   - Imported `SpeedInsights` from `@vercel/speed-insights/next` (Next.js-specific entry point)
   - Placed the component inside the `<body>` tag alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component
   - This ensures Speed Insights will track performance metrics across all pages

3. **Framework Compatibility**: The implementation follows the official Next.js App Router pattern for Next.js v13.5+ projects, which is appropriate for this project running Next.js 16.2.3.

### Verification

- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ All existing tests pass (7 tests in ThemeProvider.test.tsx)
- ✅ No new linting errors introduced (pre-existing linting issues in other files remain unchanged)
- ✅ TypeScript compilation successful
- ✅ Lock file properly updated

### Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel, Speed Insights will need to be enabled in the Vercel dashboard to begin tracking performance metrics. The component is now ready and will automatically start collecting data once activated on the platform.

### Implementation Pattern

The SpeedInsights component was added in the same location and style as the existing Analytics component, maintaining consistency with the project's architecture. Both Vercel integrations are now properly configured at the root layout level.
